"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$/dummyroot/FTL/event[@name=\"FR_TARTARUS_EMPTY_CHAOS\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:758
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/destroyed/text"
msgstr ""
"As the ship breaks apart, strange symbols flash before your eyes, making you"
" dizzy and confused."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:760
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/destroyed/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:765
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/deadCrew/text"
msgstr ""
"You expected literal demons to be harder to kill, though it seems whatever "
"they are made out of is still just as vulnerable as living crew are."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:767
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/deadCrew/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:779
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"You reach the spot labled as the \"bonus bounty\". As expected, a vessel of unique design orbits the beacon, hailing you the moment it senses your presence. A shroud of absolute darkness masks parts of the ship's true appearance. According to legend, a vessel like this was commanded by a being known as the Prince of Darkness, a demonic spirit in the form of an Equinoid. The Prince does not speak to you, simply branding their message directly in your mind.\n"
"\t\n"
"\t\"And so, another mortal challenges me. I am from the depths of a place inconceivable, and I have seen eons pass in the blink of an eye. Your life, to me, is but a single atom in the grand design of the Multiverse. Fight well, Renegade, and impress me - you may find yourself with quite a reward.\""

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:784
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Prepare to fight!"

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:786
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/choice/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Realizing there's no way out of here without a fight, you turn on your "
"weapons and engage the ship."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:788
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE\"]/choice/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:797
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE_DEFEATED\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"You're also surprised to find a special weapon among the wreckage! You've never seen anything even remotely close to something like this before, so you assume it must be a custom model made by the strange beings.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"\t\tThe Prince manifests in front of you as you return to the ship. Before you can draw your blaster, you hear the words ring out in your head. \"Be not afraid, mortal. I come to offer your spoils of war, and to join you for the remainder of your errand. I do hope your presence will not tarnish my reputation.\""

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:801
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_PRINCE_DEFEATED\"]/crewMember"
msgstr "Prince of Darkness"

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:816
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/destroyed/text"
msgstr ""
"This absolutely massive vessel seems to have reached its limits. It seems "
"even eldritch technology can't fight forever."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:818
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/destroyed/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:823
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/deadCrew/text"
msgstr ""
"After a lot of work making sure every eldritch being was dead, you can "
"finally rest for a moment when you see Tririac go down and not instantly get"
" back up."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:825
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//ship[@name=\"FR_SHIP_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/deadCrew/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:841
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"You reach the spot labled as the \"bonus bounty\". As expected, a vessel of unique design orbits the beacon, hailing you the moment it senses your presence. Its lights begin to draw your mind in, and you can barely resist its allure. There is no legend attached to this vessel, nor is there any hull design you could imagine it'd be even remotely close to.\n"
"\n"
"\tThe being in charge of the vessel begins to speak, the very words sending your brain into searing pain, migraines pushing their way through your head. \"CHILD OF MAN. DO NOT RESIST THE CALL.\"\n"
"\n"
"\t\"SUBMIT.\"\n"
"\n"
"\tWarning: This ship might prove extremely difficult if not impossible to fully clear out this enemy's crew if you don't have a reliable way to mind control, burn and/or stun enemies. Don't be afraid to skip this enemy if you aren't ready for it."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:850
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/choice[1]/text"
msgstr "Prepare to fight!"

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:852
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/choice[1]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"Realizing there's no way out of here without a fight, you turn on your "
"weapons and engage the ship."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:855
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/choice[1]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:861
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/choice[2]/text"
msgstr "Back away."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:863
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/choice[2]/event/text"
msgstr "This ship is way too powerful for you. Better to leave them be."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:865
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC\"]/choice[2]/event/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:873
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC_DEFEATED\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"You're also surprised to find a special weapon among the wreckage! You've never seen anything even remotely close to something like this before, so you assume it must be a custom model made by the strange beings.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"\tThe strange entity in command begins to manifest in front of you, and you brace yourself for a mental assault unlike anything you've ever seen. But... it doesn't come, and the burly being simply retreats into the bowels of the ship. Perhaps... they will work with you, for now."

#: src-en/data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml:877
msgid ""
"data/events_fr_sector_chaotic_tartarus.xml$//event[@name=\"FR_CHAOS_REVENANT_TRIRIAC_DEFEATED\"]/crewMember"
msgstr "Tririac"
